The placeholder `?` is used when you want to provide a parameter as the 2nd argument for `rawQuery()`, something like:

    Cursor cursordel = DB1.rawQuery(
        &quot;Select * from Userdetails WHERE Profile = ?&quot;, 
        new String[] {&quot;{1ABC#428#240#12}&quot;}
    );
which will return the rows of the table where `Profile` is equal to `{1ABC#428#240#12}`.&lt;br/&gt;

If you want to get all the rows of the table you should remove the `WHERE` clause and pass `null` as the 2nd argument for `rawQuery()`:

    Cursor cursordel = DB1.rawQuery(&quot;Select * from Userdetails&quot;, null);

